D.q[4985] = "";
D.q[7893] = "Thanks. I can\'t talk about it right now, it\'s too risky.\nAs soon as everything\'s ready, I\'ll let you know what I want you to do, but in the meantime, don\'t breathe a word to anyone, understood?";
D.q[2752] = "The traditional Pandawushu attire consists of a traditional cape and a Pandawushu headband. Every tailor on Pandala knows how to make these clothes...\nYou must wear this outfit whenever you pass a level. So, take great care of it!";
D.q[5866] = "";
D.q[5865] = "";
D.q[2220] = "So? Did the charming Ma Cleopatra give you the Subosycold?";
D.q[2418] = "Which one?";
D.q[689] = "And the final question,\nbefore evaluating the situation.\nOf cuddles we are speaking.\nMorning, midday or evening ?\n";
D.q[1261] = "And what do you need that for? Let me guess... Ah, it\'s for Amayiro\'s Tabi. So this is Oto\'s new little game.\nWell, I don\'t mind giving you one but it will cost you 1,000 Kamas.";
D.q[7894] = "I have to maintain the plumbing system, look after the snowplow, make new tools...so basically I\'m overwhelmed. However, if you could find a way of freeing up some of my time I could possibly start decorating the inside of the ice houses. What do you think?";
D.q[2419] = "Which job in particular?";
D.q[424] = "Enutrofs are the main Shovel lovers. They love digging the ground searching for treasures and protecting themselves with their tool.\nShovels can cause important damage, but require much luck to be handled.\nShovel Smiths use the Shovel Smith Hammer.";
D.q[5867] = "";
D.q[7895] = "I\'m working on two new prototypes for raising things. The plans are finished, but I don\'t have time to do anything with them. Find me a builder who can make these prototypes and bring them to me.";
D.q[5023] = "";
D.q[5868] = "";
D.q[1412] = "Theee cuulpriiit iis ammonng theem, I knnoww iit! Iiif yoouu dooon\'t knnoow, jjuuustt bee hoonnesstt and saaayyy iiitt!";
D.q[5099] = "";
D.q[7896] = "The person who made this did a pretty good job and has certainly saved me a lot of time. Take these few Kamas, you\'ve earned them.\nTell Mac Gayver to come and see me in my workshop to discuss his needs. We can also use the time to try to find a solution to the isolation of the sunken village... Actually, forget that and just tell Mac Gayver to come over.";
D.q[826] = "There are Chafers in the cemetery smarter than the idiots we have round here. Go beat some of them up and bring me back their helmets. I\'ll need 10 of them. With those on, our Chafers might survive more than a few minutes in battle...";
D.q[1175] = "A bit too slow...\nBut you can try again.";
D.q[645] = "There are numerous gods in our universe. You chose your beliefs a long time ago and you master a couple of techniques, but you still have a way to go.\n\nYou can lead your life and career as you want, every trade has its value.\n\nSome prefer to fight, others have a profession and others again do the two at the same time. There is no wrong way of evolving, only choices to make. \n\nYou can get more information on your characteristics by clicking on the round pictogram of the DNA strand on the bottom interface, on the top right of your portrait. At each level up, you gain 5 characteristic points to share out among wisdom, vitality, strength, intelligence, agility and chance.";
D.q[7897] = "Our Mayor\'s reaction doesn\'t surprise me. It\'s up to us to show her she\'s wrong. As for Valy Domidat, I\'ll call in to see her next time I\'m at the village.\nWe\'ve got quite a few sick patients here and I\'m afraid we\'ll have some more coming in soon. The Lurgi epidemic is spreading.\nFind Herr Peece, the village doctor, and ask him for thirty vaccines. Aurora will pay him later.";
D.q[4846] = "";
D.q[7903] = "I don\'t want to hear about Count Harebourg, or about farming any more.\nAurora Borealis wishes to use the reopening of a seaway to the continent to develop tourism on the island. She has developed the interesting concept of an ice village, which I backed straight away. So, we could actually rake in some profit from this eternal winter.";
D.q[2425] = "There are many types of blacksmith, one for each sort of forged weapon: swords, daggers, shovels, hammers, axes, they\'re all forged by a smith with unique training and skill. Lots of metals and some wood are needed for these professions. As with all the profession, you\'ll need a fair amount of money and knowledge to improve your skills, but when a bloodthirsty adventurer hands over a ton of hard earned Kama for one of your lethal tools, all your toils will be justified.";
D.q[6660] = "There are many advantages. All militiamen in a city share the same alignment and benefit from the following: they can conquer villages and gain access to their exclusive resources. They\'re also able to place Prisms of Conquest to align areas, which can increase their gains during fights and harvests if they decide to actively take part in the battle against the other alignment. Finally, when they obtain a high enough rank within their alignment, they can choose a specialisation and receive new abilities. The specialisations are warrior, spy and priest. Choosing an alignment has other small advantages too, like being able to travel via prisms, aggressing enemies etc. You\'ll find out more about that later but for the moment go and earn your spurs and come back when you\'ve got a bit more experience, I might have a tip for you.";
D.q[7898] = "I haven\'t got that much, it\'s not a pharmacy here you know... Ah, it\'s Aurora Borealis who\'s sent you. How is she? She needs thirty doses of Lurgi vaccine? No problem, here you go. Say hi to her for me.";
D.q[7904] = "I haven\'t seen any hunters around here. It\'s been pretty quiet for a few days.";
D.q[3210] = "Woah! Seriously, I\'m impressed! You managed to defeat that terrible creature! Lady Luck is on your side, that\'s for sure! I still can\'t believe someone like you, able to lose their way in such a simple labyrinth, was actually able to bring down the Minotoror. I\'m pretty sure you wouldn\'t last a minute if you were to face the real master, the Minotot! Anyway...\nWhat do you want now?";
D.q[4896] = "The Hammer of Light? That means nothing to me. You should ask in the other Temples, maybe they can help you.";
D.q[7905] = "We have nothing to fear here. The craters which form the lake only represent a small part of the geothermic activity on the island, at least that\'s what the experts say.\nHowever, there is still an active volcano at the centre of the island, no-one goes there and I would recommend you keep away from it too.";
D.q[1668] = "Very simple, 3 balloons, 3 swords. When you\'ve lined a sword up with a balloon, click anywhere on the screen to throw it.\nBurst all 3 balloons and you get the jackpot!";
D.q[3159] = "Get out of here you Cave Gobball! How dare you ruin my sumptuous hairdo before this fight? I pray that Silvosse turns you into a Wild Sunflower or into a stiff-bristled Kirball seed.";
D.q[1735] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[4897] = "How much do you want to bet that I know something?\nI see, you do not want to play... Anyway, I know nothing about it.";
D.q[4998] = "Did you find anything?";
D.q[7906] = "I haven\'t seen that idiot for a while, thankfully!";
D.q[6406] = "Are you joking? The Cania Plains stretch on to infinity, which means that there is also an infinite number of Kanigers.";
D.q[4898] = "I\'ve never heard of a Hammer of Light. You don\'t mean Turkish Delight, do you?";
D.q[2052] = "Head over to Dragonsly the alchemist. Once the metal is transmuted, the Xelor magic will be annihilated!";
D.q[7901] = "There\'s no point insisting, I don\'t want to talk about it.";
D.q[6252] = "Stand in front of th Zaapi and tell him to stand right in front of me. I want to make sure that it\'s a recruit who\'s qualifying for service.";
D.q[500] = "You awe looking fow the exit?\nI can telepowt you somewhewe else if you want...";
D.q[3118] = "I\'m very impressed, little one! You defeated my pets.\nI think I ought to try and bring you back to life now.\nI\'ll swap a resurrection powder and your ghost body for a resurrection, but it will only be effective once you\'re out of here. Then, you\'ll be with your master again.";
D.q[5414] = "";
D.q[1688] = "Give me 10 Kamas and I\'ll give you a fishing rod. Then you have one chance to catch a Quaquack. If you manage to catch one, come and give it to me and I\'ll give you a prize!";
D.q[6812] = "Why, are you interested? Hehe, just kidding. He wanted to take me to Ufot Eticili\'s house to do something or other. He talked about gambling and fighting Tofus, and that he wanted to enjoy the night because it\'s supposedly the busiest time. Nothing interesting really.";
D.q[3654] = "There\'s no doubt about it, if you want a recommendation from me, I\'ve to know you\'ve a head on those shoulders.";
D.q[4991] = "How did the fight start?";
D.q[1579] = "Congratulations! You\'re among the first ones to bring me back ten badges.";
D.q[7902] = "";
D.q[2248] = "*Passing her hands through her hair* Yes? Can I help you?";
D.q[598] = "Congratulations dear guest! You\'ve just acquired a direct outward journey to the tropical islands! You\'ll lose an hour, gain an hour. This is your life, and it\'s ending one minute at a time so enjoy it. Put your helmet and your wings on. Arrange to meet your friends and hop in the cannon. Within a few minutes you\'ll reach your destination. Enjoy your holiday! Just think... if you wake up at a different time, in a different place, could you wake up as a different person?";
D.q[7339] = "";
D.q[1684] = "Congratulations, you have brilliffically defeaten this monster, but will you be able to do the same with the next one?\nNow you have to choose, leave and take your prize or continue the adventure!";
D.q[7340] = "";
D.q[5450] = "";
D.q[4699] = "Certainly. There you go, it\'s done.";
D.q[7072] = "Salutations! I see you\'re surprised to be talking to a plant. I suppose you usually take a hoe to creatures like me. Gosh, it\'s not often you see a warrior with a bit of spirit. As my Root says to me often - How much is between what we think and what we say. I\'m not saying anything about what you do, but...";
D.q[3659] = "Thank you my dear. I had all the ingredients, I just needed the recipe. Here, this is for you.";
D.q[5428] = "";
D.q[623] = "Do you believe, talking is all what it takes to practice this profession? I don\'t think you understood the essence of this profession. If you really wish to become an alchemist, go to see my colleague instructor. He must be studying speckled stones at three leagues North-West from the Kanojedo temple.";
D.q[5451] = "East of here you\'ll find a cave. Anyone can enter, but I only allow a few special people to use the teleportation portal. What\'s more, the portal can only be activated by four people I trust. If you want to use it, first of all find three other people who, like you, have saved a Bow Meow from certain death.";
D.q[5458] = "";
D.q[5690] = "Wonderful! I\'ll put it away somewhere safe. Make the most of your free time by finding out about the benefits that your new rank, Master of Scrolls, brings you.";
D.q[1080] = "Hey you, what do you want?";
D.q[2839] = "Greetings #1! You look as radiant as a phoenix, young disciple.\nWhat can I do for you?\n";
D.q[3538] = "Hey there, Enutrof Friend! Fighting isn\'t your strong point, have you noticed? Ha... When you\'re a bit more experienced and your god has blessed you with strength, you\'ll be fearsome. Until then, here\'s a little task you can carry out for me.";
D.q[4856] = "You should go see Amayiro, he\'s been feeling pretty miserable since one of Silvosse\'s disciples was convicted of treason.";
D.q[6183] = "You seem very enthusiastic, so I\'ll let you off the chore of having to equip the new recruits for training. However, to make things more official, I want you to head to the Amakna militia to pick up an Alignment Conversion Certificate.";
D.q[6304] = "Salutations, it seems to me that I asked you for the soul of a Vampire Master in exchange for the information you need.";
D.q[5391] = "";
D.q[3618] = "With Piwi feather me stuff beer in me!";
D.q[7648] = "Are you still alive? I\'m not the vindictive type, so I\'ll give you an item that belonged to Goultard during his childhood. Which one would you like?";
D.q[7908] = "Thanks to our efforts, the seaway to Abakna has been reopened. It\'s a great accoblishment!\nIf we carry on bike that, we should banage to thaw the port completely and give it back some of its glory of yesteryear.";
D.q[1844] = "*The Bow Meow smells the mimilk, laps it up a little bit, then empties its bowl*\n*It then resumes its melancholy complaint*\nMeeeooow";
D.q[1191] = "Let\'s see... It seems you\'ve started to train with this brave Amayiro.\nIt might be time for you to choose an order and to specialise in a field to serve best the interests of Bonta!\n\nI\'m part of the Valiant Heart Order myself. If you wish to know more about another order, I recommend you visit the other floors of the tower...";
D.q[6276] = "Huh... not much for me.";
D.q[4906] = "";
D.q[7649] = "You want more? No problem, it amuses me to see my little darlings tear bullies like you to pieces.";
D.q[7909] = "I developed an athlete\'s physique by loading tons and tons of barrels of cereal. Since we don\'t export anything anybore, I now deal in the transport of heavy baterials, especially planks and betal which are used in plumbing.";
D.q[4652] = "Pnj(183) et Message(4649)";
D.q[4249] = "Pnj(961) et Message(4247)";
D.q[1845] = "*He might be hungry now* \n*You should find out what a Bow Meow eats and go get some*";
D.q[6998] = "So that\'s how I was able to gather souls for Otomai in record time, and when my fingers touched the reward, I had an epiphany.\nThe real power was to be able to gather companions from all backgrounds for a common cause, and to live the human adventure. When I realised this, I asked Otomai to give the reward to someone else.\nTo me, the human spirit is much stronger than any Dofus, and the power of all the Dofus together could never match what happened that day.";
D.q[4982] = "";
D.q[5943] = "";
D.q[7651] = "Help me! These cruel Bworks want to roast me and use my bones to make table legs. That huge Bwork over there is the one keeping me prisoner.";
D.q[7910] = "It\'s useful, but its effects wear off too quickly. While we\'re on the subject, I\'ve got the threat of an epidemic on my hands. Emi, a young employee of Circey Real, is responsible for the distribution of Frosteez but she\'s fallen ill. I\'m already taking care of her case, but I have a big problem: she will have contaminated all those she\'s been in contact with. Can you go around and make sure all the people she\'s had contact with and who are presenting symptoms of a bad case of the Lurgi have been vaccinated? I already have too much to do here myself.";
D.q[4293] = "Refused, huh? I knew it wouldn\'t be so easy. Bu I\'m sure that he\'ll change his mind if we find something very precious to show to him. I know his type - he won\'t be able to say no if he actually has the object under his nose. \nWe just need to find a precious object. A jewel should do the trick. Go see Brakmar\'s jeweller, Milone Corichel, and ask him what kind of jewels he likes. Then go ask Milone Corichel to make you one.";
D.q[7034] = "You want to visit the Isle O\'Anstitch? You\'re one Gobball short of a herd, aren\'t you, unless you\'ve got Iop blood in your veins... Well, I\'ll give you a pass, but it will cost you 3,000 Kamas.\nThat\'s expensive, you say? Yeah? Well, you should check out the competition.\nAh yes, I forgot, there is no competition, ahahah.";
D.q[1212] = "You need to practice some more.\nGo and see Oto Mustam again.";
D.q[1521] = "Are you sure? Are you just wishing for your enemies\' death and not for everyone else\'s?";
D.q[7652] = "Grabumph!";
D.q[7911] = "You\'re very kind. Here\'s the list of people concerned and the place where you\'re most likely to find them.\nWhen you\'ve administered all the vaccines, come back here to let me know.";
D.q[3986] = "Glowious! I\'m glowious! By the way, I fowgot to ask you: what bwought you to these hostile lands.";
D.q[4902] = "Let me take a look.\nWell, it says that you need a piece of wood torn from the backside of a Dark Treechnid. It must be carved according to the instructions herein so that its magic will open the passage leading to the Hammer of Light. It also states that many people must work together to open the gate that holds the vampire prisoner.\nThe crypt is located underground in the Amakna Cemetery.\nI think you know everything now, so find a carver able to carve the piece of wood torn from a Dark Treechnid, and ask your companions to help you open the crypt and defeat the vampire.";
D.q[5439] = "";
D.q[3870] = "Pnj(893) et Message(3869)";
D.q[7653] = "Wot you want? You want skinny girl? Grumph?";
D.q[7912] = "Bank you, I was just starting to get a headache.";
D.q[7654] = "You strong, you take girl for snack.";
D.q[4993] = "";
D.q[4916] = "My hammer? You\'ve found my hammer? *the spirit glows for a moment*\nNo, I refuse to go back while I still haven\'t got my doll!";
D.q[1023] = "Well done! You\'ll soon know Brakmar like the back of your hand!";
D.q[5676] = "Good work. I hope that will dissuade any militiamen who plan to run off to the enemy camp. You showed courage and determination. As of now you\'re a Renegade Hunter. Congratulations!";
D.q[5441] = "";
D.q[7913] = "It\'s not dangerous, this thing?\nAh, well if Rose Line herselb has tested and approbed it, I have no reason to wobby about side effects.";
D.q[6031] = "";
D.q[2598] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[4921] = "Thanks but I already have everything I need.";
D.q[7914] = "It\'s annoying, by nose is perbanently running. It\'s preventing be from getting a good night\'s sleep and buh neighbours are cobplaining about by snoring.";
D.q[6045] = "";
D.q[6040] = "";
D.q[4873] = "";
D.q[304] = "There\'s no case too big, no case too small...";
D.q[3142] = "You\'re back at last!\nWell, you have all four brooches. This is sufficient proof of the trust the four sisters have in you. Besides, you wouldn\'t dare fool me, would you?\nNo one fools the great Frivolak, no one!";
D.q[3800] = "Aha... HA! Nipper\'s back for his bashing!?";
D.q[7915] = "That needle\'s a bit big, isn\'t it? Don\'t you have a smaller one? Or some pills?\nNo, but do I really hab to brick byself wib that? What a shabe...";
D.q[4455] = "Aaaargh!";
D.q[2590] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[5200] = "";
D.q[7657] = "My job really isn\'t easy, I should reconsider my career choice.";
D.q[5482] = "I\'m Lina, a proud mercenary from Astrub. People reported a suspicious funny goblin in the area... I\'m on the case.";
D.q[5363] = "";
D.q[7916] = "I should shut by shop while I recober, but I don\'t hab anyone to replace be and look after by custobers.";
D.q[5086] = "";
D.q[7917] = "I\'b not an drug addict! Go and take your nonsense elsewhere. Oh, it\'s the doctor who\'s giben you this vaccine? I\'b so sorry, I seeb to have bistaken you for sobone else. Thank Herr Peece on by behalf.";
D.q[4927] = "That\'s not my teddy bear, mine was much less beautiful. Finally, I win for a change.\nI agree to follow you to my hammer, but if things go badly for you, I\'ll come back here.";
D.q[5183] = "";
D.q[7918] = "Damned Lurgi! Anyone would think the Goddess Eniripsa had turned her back on us. When I think about Count Harebourg, safe in his castle, while we\'re fighting to survive down here - it turns by stobach!";
D.q[3776] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[4931] = "I don\'t have the time to chat with you!";
D.q[4933] = "";
D.q[1594] = "Bhat bo you want buman ? How bo you bare to bisturb this bame?";
D.q[5003] = "";
D.q[2596] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[5467] = "Ha-ha! You also find it funny? Me like funny stories...\nBut me not understand story...\nYou can explain me?";
D.q[5349] = "";
D.q[239] = "Hee-Hee! I knew it! You\'re lost, aren\'t you? The exit? I don\'t know. I\'ve been looking for it for years... Enough already! Stop smiling like that! I know where I am. I\'m... hem... Oohh I don\'t know.";
D.q[7919] = "Why is the needle so long? It\'s not the size that counts though.\nNo need to get excited, I can use it all by byself.";
D.q[7920] = "I\'m not crying, I\'ve got a runny nose.";
D.q[2486] = "\"Go find some Amber!\", Manganese said. Well, easier said than done. Where on earth can I find Amber? On trees, they said. But which trees? Please help me, my friend, I\'ll give you a Small Vitality Scroll...";
D.q[2589] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[6050] = "";
D.q[4962] = "";
D.q[191] = "The hideout of the Rogues\' Brotherhood is well-concealed and above all well-protected. It\'s surrounded by water. Plus, the way in is situated in a particularly dangerous area guarded by members of the Brotherhood.\n\nOnly the cruellest people can hope to gain access to this hideout and meet the Master of the Rogues\' Brotherhood.";
D.q[746] = "Don\'t bother me now, I\'m deep in meditation.";
D.q[6049] = "";
D.q[7921] = "You\'be cobe all this way to bring be the vaccine? Isn\'t that sweet of you.";
D.q[372] = "Finally, someone brave! Bring me 75 Prespic Peak, 75 Crab Pincer, 45 Rib Chops and 30 Flint. I\'ll make solid shields with them, shields with cutting edges like razor blades. They\'re perfect to protect oneself, efficient in attack, easy to sell at an expensive price. A dream come true!\nI\'ll give you a Great Strength Scroll in exchange.";
D.q[4926] = "Hello noble citizen. I was right to summon you, for once Amayiro didn\'t take too long passing on the information. Come closer, I do not want eavesdroppers to hear what I have to say.";
D.q[7922] = "At beast, when it was hot, we didn\'t have the problem of runny noses. You wouldn\'t have a bissue I could use, by any chance?";
D.q[837] = "HA-HA-HA, I heard Sbab\'s shrieks from here, ha-ha! Wonderful! You\'re worthy to stand by my side. If you keep up, you could even overshadow me, ha-ha-ha!\nEnough of this joking, I haven\'t heard anything from Raaga. He\'s one of our finest soldiers and he was supposed to come back from the mines in the north today to report on the lava up there. Go find him... but above all, find the report.";
D.q[4559] = "Do you have my shells?";
D.q[5817] = "";
D.q[5379] = "";
D.q[5018] = "";
D.q[7923] = "Oh, I\'b neber seen such a long one, it\'s ibpressive! And do you know how to use it? You can use it on be, that\'s not a problem.";
D.q[374] = "What are Ribs for? Not for shields anyway... it\'s for lunch dummy.";
D.q[5263] = "";
D.q[3443] = "A special dish? Who do you think I am? I mean, there\'s meatballs, yes, but no one knows how to cook them. There\'s Filtounga too, but it\'s rare. Even Greedovores can\'t finish it. I don\'t have the recipe. Go and ask Mouss Bouff. He\'ll have it.";
D.q[5322] = "";
D.q[445] = "There are only two solutions, training or characteristic scrolls. The problem with scrolls is that they\'re useless when you\'re too powerful - which is my problem. If you want, I\'ll give you a Small Strength Scroll for 100 Mush Mush Thorns.";
D.q[7925] = "The Pingwins are our friends. It\'s important to love them. That\'s what my mother used to sing to me when I was a child. I adored my mother.\nShe didn\'t survive the big freeze. It\'s Count Harebourg\'s fault.";
D.q[4981] = "";
D.q[6613] = "";
D.q[4976] = "";
D.q[4026] = "A Wabbit transformation potion! Hey, you\'re the second person to ask me this today...The last guy had done some research, but the recipe didn\'t work out, so we have to start the whole thing all over again. Can you go and visit my colleagues in Amakna?";
D.q[7926] = "The mass arrival of avid war adventurers is dangerous for the Pingwin species, who live around the ice lake.\nAt the rate they\'re massacring them, I\'m afraid that ten years for now, at most, their species will be extinct. We need to save them at all costs, and you can help me with it.";
D.q[6003] = "";
D.q[6615] = "";
D.q[6614] = "";
D.q[4989] = "";
D.q[5008] = "";
D.q[3225] = "I can also tell you more about the Porcos Rustos!\nThey\'re coarse stubborn boors and they only live to satisfy their primary needs: eating, drinking and bathing in the mud!\nWhat else can I say? Right! They don\'t trust creatures that don\'t have a snout in the middle of their faces...";
D.q[7927] = "I have a large estate on which I can keep dozens of Pingwins. Ideally I would need some females to ensure the reproduction of the species. Could you catch six of them and bring them to me safe and sound? I will compensate you for the risk you\'re taking.";
D.q[5392] = "";
D.q[4456] = "(By the look of him, he won\'t see the end of the week. Or the day. Or even the hour.)";
D.q[7928] = "Thank you. She\'ll be safe with me. Hurry up and save the others.";
D.q[5422] = "";
D.q[5199] = "";
D.q[5290] = "";
D.q[7929] = "You did well. If, one day, the Pingwins at the lake do die out, their species will live on on my estate thanks to you.\nSo, just one more little Mama Pingwin and I\'ll leave you in peace.";
D.q[5201] = "";
D.q[5432] = "";
D.q[6271] = "What are you doing there?";
D.q[138] = "(Grizmine puts the die in the Bronze tankard, moves the tankards around very quickly, and the die seems to pass from one tankard to another but there\'s no logical explanation for it)\n\nSo which tankard is the die in, my friend ?";
D.q[7930] = "So, as agreed, 4 dozen Pingwin eggs for the pub and about 15 old Mama Pingwins for the butcher. Well, have you got all that?\nWhat am I doing? Erm... well... you see... These eggs and dead birds? It\'s nothing, nothing at all... Please, don\'t tell the militia.";
D.q[4143] = "Hello! I\'m Polka Merer, one of Otomai\'s most famous assistants.\nI\'m making sure that these paddocks are running smoothly. We sometimes use them to observe the behaviour of the creatures of the island when they\'re in captivity. Unfortunately, I don\'t have a single breeding machine free and I can\'t continue my research without one.";
D.q[4576] = "Any news?";
D.q[5323] = "Go get some rest and come and see me afterwards.";
D.q[7931] = "Please don\'t tell the militia. Yes, I\'ve got caves filled with Mama Pingwins which I battery farm for their eggs and their meat. But, please understand, because of Count Harebourg\'s invention, we went from being the last word in agriculture to the last word in famine overnight.";
D.q[7428] = "";
D.q[632] = "If you\'re looking for some recipes, you should go to the library. An alchemist created an encyclopaedia of more than 12 books about rare recipes.";
D.q[636] = "If you\'re looking for recipes, you should go to the library. An alchemist created an encyclopedia composed of more than 12 books about rare recipes.";
D.q[7934] = "Bambelle does exactly as she pleases. If she carries on like this, ten years from now there won\'t be any trees left to cut down.";
D.q[4590] = "";
D.q[4586] = "";
D.q[6814] = "Meoww ... vroom vroom.";
D.q[6004] = "";
D.q[6619] = "";
D.q[291] = "Hello, I\'m Kwaker Vans, but you can call me Legend. That idiotic impostor Kelog Hornflex has taken my position as number one bread merchant in Amakna, but I\'m preparing a counter-attack: Curryless Curry Bread!";
D.q[2715] = "Wrong! All wrong! I don\'t think you came here to become a Pandikaze...";
D.q[7932] = "Thanks, I knew you weren\'t insensitive and would understand.\nTake this Purse of Kamas and don\'t change your mind.";
D.q[7935] = "I\'ve had an excellent idea which would fight deforestation, while still allowing the lumberjacks to do their job. If we replant a tree every time we chop one down and we take into account the amount of time they need to grow, we should be able to determine how many trees to cut down every year without risking deforestation.\nBambelle\'s given us the go ahead, so we can start planting seeds. Do you want to help?";
D.q[6620] = "";
D.q[7933] = "What? An illegal Pingwin farm? For the love of Cra, I\'m not going to let that happen! Bonnie, look after the shop, I\'m going Pingwin hunting.";
D.q[5251] = "(You have the impression the Divad is briefly disturbed when you show him the earring, and even a little panicked. Is it only an impression?)\nHmm, I can see that this earring belongs to...to...";
D.q[7936] = "I\'m going to tell you where to plant them. Pay attention on the way though, you might be attacked by wild animals who want to eat your seeds, defend their territory or simply eat you.\nCome back to see me when you\'ve planted all your seeds.";
D.q[3222] = "Are you scared little piggy? Don\'t worry... Stop whining and I\'ll take you out of here. I\'ll even give you a new saved point as you seem to have forgotten yours. So let me see what\'s left... Weebblyz Head? No it wouldn\'t be interesting for you... your butt is too soft! The Odgean Stables? No, too horrifying... Gorgor\'s Den? No, way too dangerous...\nWell, I\'ll choose for you and it will be....... the Zaap of the Castle of Amakna! You should feel right at home!";
D.q[1042] = "*Jingle* *Gle,Jingle* *Jingle*-*Jinjingle*, *JinJingle*";
D.q[1356] = "*Scissors*\nTough luck, you\'ve lost...";
D.q[1115] = "*That man gives you an icy look and doesn\'t say a word*";
D.q[1848] = "*The Bow Meow looks exhausted. It sits back, looks around and meows again*\nMeoooww";
D.q[1355] = "*Paper*\nTough luck, you\'ve lost...";
D.q[7937] = "You\'re finished already and you got out safe and sound? My heart rejoices to hear it.\nWith this new system, the forest is only going to get better, which will have a positive effect on our ecosystem. That, at least, is useful and environmentally friendly, not like the excessive exploitation of local agriculture.";
D.q[4804] = "Hello, I heard that you were investigating the treason of Kit Dingaround. Well, it goes without saying that he\'s guilty. In fact, I\'ll reward you well if you tell the court this version of events.";
D.q[345] = "Hello, I found a scroll in the attic of my grandmother\'s place...I don\'t know what it\'s for, but I\'m sure it will help someone who\'s smarter than me. I\'ll exchange it for 120 Moskito Brows. I collect those brows, very useful things they are...";
D.q[1426] = "Hi #1! Will you give me a hand tonight ?\nI need 10 Tofu legs. Try to find a hunter who will agree to sell you some!";
D.q[2920] = "Greetings, I didn\'t even notice you coming. Your accomplices are getting better, that\'s great.\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[5285] = "The trial is over, there\'s no reason for you to still be in my court.";
D.q[330] = "Heeey, great! With this under me, my backside won\'t get cold anymore! Thank you! What a great present! Very well, now you can get nice and personal with this hole here.";
D.q[2294] = "*The Gobball drinks the beer... ho ho hum... then it EATS THE GLASS waheyyy* Belch...Hic... Smash!";
D.q[7938] = "Someone, at last! While I was tracking a Skrat, I surprised two Kanigloos in the act of the reproduction of the species. They didn\'t appreciate being disturbed and they really taught me a lesson.\nI managed to drag myself here but I\'m too weak to go on. Can you take me to Herr Peece\'s house? He\'s the village doctor.";
D.q[245] = "Well, you seem determined to die. It\'s your choice, but you\'ll still have to prove you can fight before I let you past. Bring me the nail of a Karne Rider. Their smell chases away a great number of monsters and will protect me. If you\'re able to remove the nail of one of those proud lunatics, then I\'ll know I can let you past.";
D.q[5635] = "*Thinking* I think so hard that people around me can read my mind.";
D.q[2297] = "*singing to herself in the style of Pest on a Child*\nHey boy, comin up to me with that hair, \nget away from me boy, \nI ain\'t cuttin your hair, no boy, \nyou ain\'t rich enough... BOY";
D.q[1461] = "How long?\nThe date of imprisonment is clearly written on the detention form you were given when you arrived. You\'re imprisoned for an hour, now can you figure the rest out for yourself?";
D.q[7939] = "It\'s no use, the others got here first?\nHow come you\'re not with them?\nWho am I talking about? Those scoundrels who took me by surprise when I was hunting the Glacial Boar. They clobbared me, swiped my bags and my weapons and left me alone in the cold. I\'m too weak to get back to the village by myself. Can you take me to the doctor?";
D.q[2296] = "*humming*\nWe\'ll catch a Moowolf and a fox, and put them in a box...";
D.q[6621] = "";
D.q[6622] = "";
D.q[5024] = "";
D.q[7940] = "You\'ll never guess what happened to me. I was chasing the ash Frighogs when I saw something move. I fired an arrow, it was my Bow Wow... At the same moment, a rock fell from the wall and squashed my leg.\nI need your help to get back to Frigost. It\'s a miracle I\'m still alive at all.";
D.q[6623] = "";
D.q[4225] = "Hello. My name is Scroll Tom, if you need a scroll, I\'m your man.\nI can also let you try many potions for unlearning characteristics and spells.";
D.q[3554] = "Thanks, females be happy.";
D.q[329] = "I see... you\'re really stubborn. Oh, and if... no... but after all... I can\'t... But hey, I might as well. Okay, listen up. Bring me something to protect me against the vile creature that haunts this damp cave and I\'ll let you into the hole. Okay, now remember all this... l need Boowolf Testicles, Mush Mush Sporm and a pair of Captain Chafer\'s Leather Panties. I somehow doubt he\'ll want to eat me if I sling all that round my neck.";
D.q[1331] = "YOU AGAIN? GO AWAY! I DON\'T WANT TO SEE YOU!";
D.q[5031] = "";
D.q[4800] = "I protest, I am innocent!";
D.q[6624] = "";
D.q[1029] = "...\nYou have gone down strongly in my estimation, #1. There\'s only one thing left for you to do: warn his family about his death.\nCome back again when you\'re done, but take your time...";
D.q[2802] = "... Go away...";
D.q[5496] = "Don\'t pull that face, you look like you\'ve just seen a dead man!\nYou\'re probably wondering why I helped you, no?\nDon\'t get excited, I\'m not doing this altruistically. In fact, I was paid to follow you and make sure you weren\'t drawn into any trouble in the city of Astrub. I don\'t know what these Pandawas want from you, but you\'d be better off going to see to my employer. You\'ll have no problem recognising him, he\'s the Pandawa who welcomed you when you first arrived in the World of Twelve.";
D.q[7941] = "Another casualty!\nBetween this, the other injured patients, the patients suffering from malnutrition or chilblains and the emerging Lurgi epidemic, I\'m never going to cope with it all.\nIf only the big freeze had never happened... Mad as we were...\nOk, leave him here, I\'ll take care of him. Thanks for bringing him here.";
D.q[5212] = "";
D.q[7350] = "";
D.q[669] = "Two possibilities :\n- you can find natural Metarias in the bowels of monsters.\n- you can make them with a compressor of my creation, using resources of high elemental potential and a resistant sphere that I\'m selling at an interesting price. Every recipe is written in a book... which you can get off me.";
D.q[910] = "100";
D.q[626] = "Hello. \nWhat a magnificent little temple! I think I\'ll stay here for a little while before heading towards my next destination.";
D.q[6625] = "";
D.q[672] = "A fragment of the plinth from the most magical weapon I\'ve ever heard of. This piece of stone is impregnated with a magic essence that comes from the weapon itself and allows us to study it without causing damage.\nYou passed the test successfully. Take this magic tool, it will enable you to create magic items. Plus, here\'s a small book, some sort of aide-memoire to every creator of magic weapons.";
D.q[7942] = "Hands off! I saw it first! It\'s mine!";
D.q[3006] = "It costs 100 Kamas.";
D.q[6626] = "";
D.q[7943] = "You\'re... too late...\nMy treasure... stolen...\nIt\'s Emile... the killer... aaaaargh!";
D.q[855] = "45";
D.q[7565] = "Hmm, I\'m beginning to see things more clearly. Smugglers are selling Ouassingue Juice to unscrupulous merchants, who mix it with their drinks. With the addiction that follows, these merchants create a loyal clientele. It\'s unacceptable, the Grandapan will be beside himself when he hears what is happening! \nI heard that Dragonsly, the Eniripsa in the Astrubian Alchemist Merchant, was an outstanding alchemist. \nGo and see him and ask him if he knows of a cure for Ouassingue Juice addiction.";
D.q[2546] = "... I\'ve heard that a messenger came from the continent. Apparently he brought a Dofus on to the island... Crazy man! If the Pandikazes happen to find out who he is, he\'s a dead man... You know, with all those rebels sabotaging stuff, an accident could easily happen. *Broad grin*";
D.q[6627] = "";
D.q[1464] = "Halt! Who goes there? If you cross this bridge you\'ll find yourself in hostile territory. The village of our forefathers was situated on this peninsula. But in the year 493, a colony of Dreggons invaded it and the population fled to the North.\nArm yourself well if you want to leave this village in one piece...";
D.q[7944] = "About this treasure, of course! It\'s place is in a museum. And I\'m not just saying that because my friends say the inside of my house looks like a museum.";
D.q[768] = "58";
D.q[866] = "56";
D.q[867] = "57";
D.q[869] = "59";
D.q[3261] = "... Wha\' a bloody sissy!...\nYou\'re lucky I\'m goin\' back to Madrestam.\nGet on board.";
D.q[2829] = "...Hum... Terra Cogita made all this for one single reason.... I got it now! It\'s to prevent all this from happening again!... Maimane planned everything perfectly...\n\n*Wally takes out his notebook and draws some plans*";
D.q[1399] = "...";
D.q[770] = "60";
D.q[7945] = "Huh? Well, it\'s simple, since I can\'t carry it myself I\'m going to go and get a Snow Bow Wow sleigh.\nAh, but I can see your game, you\'re going to take advantage of my absence to rob me, aren\'t you?";
D.q[6816] = "Oh, you know, when night falls here it smells of polecats all the time. It\'s because of the sweat generated by the heat, stress and excitement of the game. It masks all other smells. You see quite a few Srams here as well.\nI\'d advise you to talk to the other regulars, they should be able to tell you more.";
D.q[2212] = "Thank you very much! But... the flooowers! Snifff, I... I really wanted to get a bunch for mummy! \nI wouldn\'t dare go back to the forest again, though... Please, could you go get four flax flowers for me to make a bouquet! It\'s not easy to pick up flowers... you have to be gentle... if you don\'t know how, ask an alchemist to give you a hand.";
D.q[2128] = "Thank you so much! You\'re so sweet!";
D.q[6629] = "";
D.q[7946] = "Let me see... I can\'t leave my treasure unattended, but I can\'t carry it by myself... I know! You can go back to the village and rent a snow Bow Wow sleigh. I\'ll look after my treasure until you return, then I\'ll share it with you. How does that sound?";
D.q[773] = "63";
D.q[4709] = "";
D.q[2354] = "...In past times, \'say there were some tough fights round Amakna... \'Am a born and bred Astrubian and \'never seen anything of the sort! \'Know things are happening over there and \'don\' t like it... Go back and see Gasdaure, \'knows more than she says!";
D.q[6630] = "";
D.q[7947] = "Stop dawdling! The spirits who lurk in this area are giving me a bad feeling and I\'ve already had to fend off several attackers before you got here.";
D.q[298] = "Thanks a lot. Now look at me straight in the eyes. I\'ll be able to see if you have a ghost of a chance of winning against the terrible Boowolf. If so, I\'ll let you pass.";
D.q[775] = "65";
D.q[874] = "64";
