D.q[889] = "79";
D.q[891] = "81";
D.q[6166] = "I have many precious gifts to offer the brave adventurers who help me find what I\'m looking for. Even I can\'t truly explain how I found these Dofus. Some say it was blind luck, others are convinced it was my destiny. But I like to think that my own hard work and research lead me to the most beautiful and dangerous prizes that exist in the World of Twelve.";
D.q[7950] = "They don\'t seem very sturdy, but, well, it\'s better than nothing. Here you go, that\'s your share.";
D.q[6633] = "";
D.q[2702] = "Hello! You ale welcome in my house! Youl eye is shining like a stal in the night: youl healt is pule... what can I do fol you?";
D.q[2965] = "Thanks a lot! Two Tofu eggs, how precious! There\'s a male and female at least? You\'re not sure? Well, you must go ask Magus Ax... He knows a lot about this World and its creatures and I needed to see him anyway... Believe it or not but I found a Dofus! You\'ll have the privilege to carry it to Magus Ax. This dragon egg seems to be extremely fragile but I don\'t know why.... Ask the Magus about it! Dofus are his specialty...";
D.q[783] = "73";
D.q[792] = "82";
D.q[801] = "91";
D.q[883] = "73";
D.q[892] = "82";
D.q[901] = "91";
D.q[902] = "92";
D.q[147] = "Oy, watch out! Stowaways get thrown overboard around these parts! \nYou don\'t have enough Kamas to come aboard my boat. Come back when you can afford it.";
D.q[784] = "74";
D.q[785] = "75";
D.q[3211] = "Ha, you don\'t even know who the Minotot is. What rock have you been living under? You remind me of those plebs who\'ve never been to the Antinau Sea or who\'ve never climbed the Church Hill. You\'re not really like them, are you?\nAnyway.... For your information, the Minotot is the real master of the house, the Minotoror is just his faithful disciple. The Minotoror uses brute force whereas the Minotot uses a powerful destructive magic. I\'m the only one to have defeated him, and that was a long time ago - so long ago that I can\'t even remember it. Actually, no one can. If you still want to confront this creature, you\'ll have to bring me the key to the room. Only a skilled Handyman will be able to help you create such a key.";
D.q[884] = "74";
D.q[885] = "75";
D.q[886] = "76";
D.q[6634] = "";
D.q[6635] = "";
D.q[7951] = "Thanks to volcanic activity on the island, the waters of the Tears of Ouronigride are loaded with minerals. I am convinced that consuming this would be better for the Frigostians than the melted snow they\'re currently drinking.\nThe biggest problem at the moment is the high concentration of sulphur, but with the appropriate treatment, I\'m sure I can make it drinkable.";
D.q[6636] = "";
D.q[1162] = "H\'m, what is it now ? Is it possible to sleep a little here ? Well, what do you want son ?";
D.q[853] = "A Bontarian assassin... The thought had never crossed my mind. What a perfect cover, a Bontarian killing another Bontarian. You must find Bontarians with impure hearts. Ask Fryda the Midnight Claw for a Sniffling Staff. Her staffs can find the smallest trace of blood on people, it will be useful.";
D.q[6815] = "Oh, you know, when night falls here it smells of polecats all the time. It\'s because of the sweat generated by the heat, stress and excitement of the game. It masks all other smells. You see quite a few Srams here as well.\nI\'d advise you to talk to the other regulars but come back after 20:00, there are usually more people here at night. And don\'t tell Amayiro I\'m here.";
D.q[4655] = "A Brakmarian? Already? En Garde!\nOh, it\'s YOU! Look, I\'ll give myself up! I\'d rather rot in a Brakmar prison than end up dead!";
D.q[7952] = "The YeCh\'Ti\'s tracks aren\'t very fresh anymore. Time\'s running out if we want to get even with him.";
D.q[4597] = "So have you decided to give me back the documents?";
D.q[2532] = "Haven\'t you seen those merchants selling the statuettes of the goddess? All those fake dragon eggs? The advisers have planned to flood the workshops of the World with cheap products made in Pandala! In the meantime, ancestral Pandawa values are going down the swanee!";
D.q[7352] = "";
D.q[7430] = "";
D.q[7953] = "Following the numerous Mastogob massacres carried out by the YeCh\'Ti, we have decided to mount a culling expedition to get rid of it once and for all.\nIts tracks have led us here and now we\'re trying to come up with a strategy to beat it.";
D.q[7353] = "";
D.q[1209] = "Did Elviana send you? I\'d like to go with you but I\'ve to find my two brothers, Aigurraf and Tabach. They\'re likely to do all sorts of crazy stuff considering their distressed state.\nYou seem to be someone I can rely on. I give you my badge, show it to Elviana.";
D.q[797] = "87";
D.q[798] = "88";
D.q[799] = "89";
D.q[800] = "90";
D.q[4421] = "A battle is taking place in the plains on the road between Bonta and Brakmar. I want you to join in and help steer our warriors to victory!";
D.q[2054] = "Trapchet... send... you? Happy... he\'s... eaten by... a plant... the bugger...\n\n*Three-Flower takes a piece of paper out of his pocket: Sorry, I lost my voice yesterday! is written on it.*\n\nI\'ve got... interesting... news.... a darrr... k... rose... fields... of the Ingalsse... bring... one... flower... of this rose... to Trapchet..!\n\nApparen...tly... odd... patterns... were... made.... in the... wheat.... you\'ll recog.....nize them... with this detail..\n\n";
D.q[7954] = "If we approach the YeCh\'Ti like that, it will spot us. Having studied its behaviour, we have noticed that it doesn\'t take any notice of snowfoux. If we could get enough snowfoux furs in good condition, we could disguise ourselves and take the YeCh\'Ti by surprise. I need your help to get enough furs. Why don\'t we do it ourselves? Because then we would reek of the scent of snowfoux blood, which could make the YeCh\'Ti suspicious.";
D.q[7955] = "Get down! They\'re going to spot us!";
D.q[1635] = "Very well, altruism is a rare virtue in our time. Plus, it\'s always good for the protection of the country to have new warriors fighting for our cities.\n\nFinal question: if a player laughs at the way you fight, or the way you look, what do you do?";
D.q[1198] = "Very good, you have yet remembered my first lesson: give the different choices a lot of thought before making your final decision.\nCome back when you\'re absolutely sure.";
D.q[802] = "92";
D.q[803] = "93";
D.q[804] = "94";
D.q[807] = "97";
D.q[903] = "93";
D.q[904] = "94";
D.q[906] = "96";
D.q[6817] = "My parents told me never to talk to strangers, and as I don\'t know you, I\'m keeping schtum.";
D.q[7956] = "Have you succeeded? I must admit you\'ve really impressed me with this.\nI shouldn\'t tell you about this, but, well...\nIf you go further south, you will come across what the rest of us, Frigostians, call the sunken village. Mayor Cantile has forbidden any contact with its inhabitants, but having spent several days in this crevasse, I\'ve come to the conclusion that their life must be even more miserable than ours. They must certainly be in need of some help so, if you decide to go there, we\'ll pretend we haven\'t seen you, so as not to cause you any trouble.";
D.q[1634] = "Very well. Indeed, there are vile beings in Amakna who unscrupulously usurp identities to plunder honest citizens like you. Never trust people who seem to be interested in your wealth.\n\nNext question: when you become a great warrior and meet a young apprentice asking for help, what will you answer?";
D.q[808] = "98";
D.q[809] = "99";
D.q[907] = "97";
D.q[908] = "98";
D.q[909] = "99";
D.q[2953] = "Pnj(163) et Message(2950)";
D.q[736] = "A colonel of the militia was transformed into a Treechnid on his way to the harbour of Amakna.\nI think he was captured and is now in the east part of the Treechnid forest. Bring him back to the tower of the Bonta magi. They will be able to heal him.";
D.q[1136] = "Hehe, I\'m a rich man!\n*Glancing at the will*\nHmm, it seems my father actually had a few debts... hum, can you help me out with a few Kamas? You\'re more or less the one to blame after all!";
D.q[2121] = "A conspiracy! The town is finished... everyone might die... Hey you... Flee! Get outta here!";
D.q[7957] = "Aaaaah, you have the Lurgi! Go away, I don\'t want to have a nose full of snot because of you.";
D.q[2317] = "Pnj(543) and Message(2312)";
D.q[7958] = "Say, you wouldn\'t happen to have any sweets or cakes made from Granola Seed, would you? No? I would also be happy with some brioche, you know.";
D.q[6463] = "Calm down, I was joking. I really don\'t want you to humiliate me any more than you have done. Give me back my hair and take the key. And don\'t you go saying anything to Hersa.";
D.q[7429] = "";
D.q[328] = "I\'m sorry, kid, but a mewling newborn would stand more of a chance than you would at the moment. Look, I don\'t want anything bad to happen to you. Come back when you\'ve trained some more and I\'ll let you in.";
D.q[599] = "Sorry but we can\'t sell you a cheaper ticket. I\'m really sorry but let me tell you that we already sell at a loss for your greatest pleasure. So save a little more and the ticket to the sun will be yours. Good luck and see you real soon!";
D.q[336] = "Sorry, I can\'t teach you this profession, you don\'t have enough practice in the other one. \nYou can\'t learn a new profession until you\'ve mastered your current one. Come back again when you\'ve improved...";
D.q[718] = "A crow stole the mayor\'s daughter\'s necklace this morning.\nIt must be fluttering about near the tower of Bonta. I know this won\'t be the most rewarding mission ever, but the young girl insisted so much...\nSince all my guys are busy, show me you\'re stronger than a crow and bring me this necklace, heh heh heh...";
D.q[7959] = "I don\'t understand why my friends won\'t let me judge the snowmonster competition. They say I\'m not allowed because I\'m taking part in it too. It\'s stupid!";
D.q[7960] = "I\'ve seen a very pretty place around here, I think I\'m going to spend a lot of time there.";
D.q[596] = "Hard hats are not compulsory in the mines but it\'s strongly recommended. I\'ve just invented a stronger type of hard hat. All you have to do is to collect 10 Black Gobball leathers, 10 linen Strings, 5 units of Gobball wool and, of course, the help of a good tailor.";
D.q[3532] = "A goblin disciple? Why not! I\'ll train him very quickly. His brain won\'t accept many spells in any case.";
D.q[3884] = "Pnj(84) et Message(3880)";
D.q[6099] = "Greetings, I see that you have grown in strength since I last saw you. Have you pitilessly massacred many Bontarians lately?";
D.q[2508] = "Just repeat to yourself 5 times, Trouble, trouble, soil and bubble, Mire turn to solid rubble! and you\'ll be cured. But I must warn you that our island can be very dangerous when it comes to happy-go-lucky adventurers!";
D.q[6379] = "Herr Palp Itane was a Wabbit who once challenged Elturt during the Cania marathon. Unfortunately, his pretentiousness and his arrogance led him straight to defeat. He never got over the humiliation inflicted by Elturt and so followed the migration of his kind to the Lenald Island where he had some semblance of revenge when he was again confronted with Elturt. Although very old now, there remains great power within him which, according to some rumours, is the result of a pact with darkness. For my part, I can\'t see Rushu or one of his henchmen having a pact with a Wabbit, no matter how powerful it is.\nHowever, after a failed coup d\'etat he took refuge on Skeleton Wabbit Island to avoid the wrath of the Wa Wabbit, which proves that he\'s not so powerful after all.";
D.q[844] = "Hemmm. After studying the map of the city over and over again, I\'ve finally found a potential weakness: the Brakmar sewers. We shall have a closer look at the whole thing. Since you\'re here, you\'ll be on fatigue duty. First of all, go have a look at the sewers and while you\'re at it kill a few rats to clear off the entry... Bring their carcasses back, we\'ll use the meat for dinner. We\'ll be 10 this evening so bring 10 carcasses at least!";
D.q[7962] = "My little brother Léon hasn\'t grown an inch in years.\nMy parents say it\'s because of Count Harebourg, but I don\'t see the link.";
D.q[131] = "Beer is made by the brewers of Amakna. There are several different kinds, depending on what cereal is used, Malt, Hops or Barley, for example. The most powerful beers can have spectacular, unexpected effects.";
D.q[2415] = "The craftspeople create useful objects from raw materials - most often bought from harvesters, but often picked up from romantic adventures whose tall tales are matched only by the contents of their pockets! As a result, it\'s a tougher profession than harvesting. For one thing it requires more investment. It\'s like they say, you have to spend some to get some.";
D.q[3015] = "The only thing I know about it\'s that they sell well... (suddenly giving you a suspicious look).";
D.q[954] = "The fort is located in the centre of the city. It\'s both the training centre and the headquarters of the militia. You\'ll have to speak to Master Amayiro if you want to join our ranks.";
D.q[7963] = "My friends and I have made snowmonsters. We wanted to have a competition to see whose monster is scariest, but we have no-one to judge it. Rufus offered but he took part in the competition so that would be cheating. Would you do it? Please?";
D.q[1176] = "A hellhound here, within the White City?\nOut of my sight!";
D.q[2185] = "A healing stone? You took too much time to bring it to me... its power returned to nature. You have to bring it to me in less than 20 minutes. Do this for me and I\'ll set it in confinement metal.";
